OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mostly cloudy start, with a
OL,6,Ffew showers clearing southwards.
OL,7,FHowever, soon brightening up during
OL,8,Fthe morning with plenty of warm
OL,9,Fsunshine developing for the afternoon.
OL,10,FThe northwesterly breeze slowly easing.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FSunshine through the evening,
OL,13,Fwith plenty of clear skies overnight.
OL,14,FPerhaps a few mist patches forming as
OL,15,Fwinds fall light during the early
OL,16,Fhours. A cooler night than of late.
OL,17,
OL,18,CFriday:FPlenty of sunshine through the
OL,19,Fday, once any morning shallow mist or
OL,20,Ffog patches clear. Feeling warmer for
OL,21,Fmany as winds remain light.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
